citing_decision_name: Minnesota v. Mille Lacs Band of Chippewa Indians,526 U.S. 172  (1999) (in part)
cited_name_full: Winters v. the United States
quote: We have held that Indian treaties are to be interpreted liberally in favor of the Indians...and that any ambiguities are to be resolved in their favor, Winters v. United States, 207 U.S. 564, 576-577 (1908)
rationale: The Acting Decision cites Winters as valid precedent and relies on its principles for treaty interpretation.
